#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:4
msgid "Privacy and Bitcoin"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:6
msgid ""
"A non-exhaustive list of reasons of why you should care about privacy in "
"Bitcoin."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:8
msgid ""
"Let’s limit it to legal activities because, in the case of illegality, I "
"believe the value of privacy is pretty straightforward."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:10
msgid "1. Personal risk"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:12
msgid ""
"If everyone knows how much money you have, criminals can decide that you are "
"a worthy target to be attacked for your money."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:14
msgid ""
"If you are lucky, the attack will be only digital but, in many known cases, "
"it gets physical as well."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:16
msgid "This puts you and your loved ones at great risk."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:18
msgid "2. Targeted ads"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:20
msgid ""
"If your finances are easily followed and, let’s say, sold to advertising "
"agencies that show you ads based on your spendings, other people besides "
"yourself might end up seeing these ads and learning what you are buying."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:22
msgid ""
"Even with legal harmless stuff, it might be a liking or a need that you’d "
"prefer to keep private."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:24
msgid ""
"There’s actually a real life example of a father learning his daughter was "
"pregnant because of the ads that were directed to her."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:26
msgid "3. Business privacy"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:28
msgid ""
"For a business, having your finances transparent and available to anyone can "
"cause serious damage."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:30
msgid ""
"Imagine if your competitors knew all about your revenues, margins, "
"suppliers, the salaries of your employers, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:32
msgid "4. Commercial leverage"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:34
msgid ""
"What if a company knew that you had a lot of money and wouldn’t hurt you to "
"pay three times the price they usually charge on a product?"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:36
msgid ""
"They could easily show “special prices” for you on their e-commerce website "
"based on how much they think you’re going to pay."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:38
msgid "Just for you"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:40
msgid "5. Miner censorship"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:42
msgid ""
"If your address is easily found and connected to you, miners can join forces "
"to censor your transactions by actively not adding it to their proposed "
"block."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:44
msgid ""
"Why would they do that? For numerous reasons, including government pressure, "
"business interest or just wanting to see the world burn."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:46
msgid "6. Fungibility"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:48
msgid ""
"Good money has to be fungible, that is, all “chunks” of money have to be "
"equally accepted no matter its origin."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:50
msgid ""
"This is the reality with cash. No one can refuse your cash or try to "
"prosecute you just because the person who paid you got the money selling "
"drugs."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:52
msgid "FUNGIBLE MONEY"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:54
msgid ""
"If it weren’t fungible, every bill would effectively be worth a different "
"value (dirty notes would be worth less than clean ones) and the money wouldn’"
"t work."
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:56
msgid "NON-FUNGIBLE MONEY"
msgstr ""

#: ./privacy-and-bitcoin/source-text.txt:58
msgid ""
"If Bitcoin has a bad privacy, this tracing of “bad money” becomes very "
"feasible and the currency won’t be fungible."
msgstr ""

